meaningMnemonic: A <kanji>name</kanji> <kanji>part of speech</kanji> is when you are naming something. What part of speech has names in it? That would be the <vocabulary>noun</vocabulary>.
readingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.
